  "system": {
    "description": "<p>You can grant a <strong>Help Die (d8)</strong> to an ally within range. The&nbsp;target can use this <strong>Help Die </strong>to add to any <strong>Check </strong>they make&nbsp;before the start of our next turn.</p>\n<p>Casting Guidance counts as taking the <strong>Help Action </strong>and still triggers the &ldquo;<strong>Multiple Action Penalty</strong> <strong>(Help)</strong>&rdquo;.&nbsp;So if you cast Guidance again or take the <strong>Help Action </strong>the <strong>Help Die </strong>would be a <strong>d6</strong>, then <strong>d4</strong>, then you would not be able to any more during the same round of <strong>Combat</strong>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Mana Point Enhancements</strong></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Sustained: (1 MP)</strong> Increase the duration to 1 minute&nbsp;but it requires Concentration.</li>\n<li><strong>Expand: (2 MP)</strong> Grant an additional Help Die (of the same size you grant with the casting of the Spell).</li>\n</ul>",
